               <head>Shiʻa-sunni polemical sectarian works (a-f)</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2012000503 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010112931">
                  <summary>A collection, called <title>Majmūʻah</title> in a pencilled note on
                            f. 1r, of Shiʻa polemical sectarian works. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 313a" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_313a-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="35r">ff. 1v-35r</locus>
                     <author key="person_f8130">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Javād ʿAlī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">جواد علی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author key="viaf_36805746">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Dildār ʻAlī, 1752 or 3-1819 or
                                    20</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">دلدار علی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23264">Naql-i khaṭṭ-i shīʻah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23264">نقل خط شیعه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Letters between Javād ʻAlī and the Shiʻa controversialist
                                        <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657192.0x000001 viaf_36805746">Dildār ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad Muʻīn
                                        al-Naṣīrābādī</persName> (d. 1820). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Also includes letters between Javād ʻAlī and other
                                    correspondents. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="https://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f005r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 5</ref>.
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 313b" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_313b-item2">
                     <locus from="35r" to="42r">ff. 35r-42r</locus>
                     <author key="person_f8371">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Qulī ibn Muḥammad
                                    Nīshāpūrī Kāntūrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد قلی ابن محمد نیشاپوری کانتوری
                                </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23265">Taṭhīr al-muʼminīn ʻan najāsat
                                al-mushrikīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23265">تطهیر المومنین عن نجاسة المشرکین</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A polemic against muftis who declare unbelievers to be ritually
                                    clean by Muftī Muḥammad Qulī ibn Muḥammad Nīshāpūrī Kāntūrī (d.
                                    1844). </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="https://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f006r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 6</ref>.
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 313c" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_313c-item3">
                     <locus from="43v" to="70r">ff. 43v-70r</locus>
                     <author key="person_f7392">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān
                                    Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد رشید الدین خان دهلوی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23266">Mabḥas̱ taḥqīq al-shīʻah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23266">مبحث تحقیق الشیعة</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A reply to an anti-sunni polemic, apparently the <title>Sayf-i Nāṣirī</title>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The title is taken from a note signed by <persName role="fmo" key="person_f7377">Muḥammad Karīm Allāh</persName> on <locus n="43r">f. 43r</locus>. The work is incomplete at the end.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f007r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 7</ref>.
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 313d" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_313d-item4">
                     <locus from="72v" to="154r">ff. 72v-154r</locus>
                     <author key="person_f7392">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān
                                    Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد رشید الدین خان دهلوی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23267">Radd-i ʻaqīdah-ʼi Ḥusām</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23267">رد عقیده حسام</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A reply by Rashīd al-Dīn Dihlavi to part of <persName key="viaf_36805746">Dildār ʻAlī</persName>'s polemic <title key="work_23073">Ḥusām al-islām</title>, itself directed against
                                        <persName role="aut" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658519.0x000001 viaf_53999017">ʻAbd al-ʻAzīz
                                        Dihlavī</persName>'s anti-Shiʻa treatise <title key="work_9203">Tuḥfah-ʼi Is̱nāʼ-ʻasharīyah</title>. The
                                    title is supplied. 
                        </p>
                        <p>A note on f. 72r is signed by <persName role="fmo" key="person_f7377">Muḥammad Karīm Allāh. </persName>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f008r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 8</ref>.
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>C.A. Storey, <title>Persian Literature: A Bio-bibliographical
                                        Survey</title>, in <title>Storey
                                            Online</title>
                           <biblScope>
                              <ref target="https://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/storey-online/31-religion-1-COM_40301000#V4-0454-005" type="n/a">, vol.IV §454(5b) </ref>
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 313e " xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_313-item5">
                     <locus from="155r" to="164v">ff. 155r-164v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>A Shiʻa response without title or author to arguments proposed in
                                        <persName key="viaf_53999017">ʻAbd al-ʻAzīz
                                        Dihlavī</persName>'s <title key="work_9203">Tuḥfah-ʼi
                                        Is̱nā-ʻasharīyah. </title>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f009r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 9</ref>.
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 313f" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_313-item6">
                     <locus from="166r" to="174v">ff. 166r-174v</locus>
                     <author key="person_f7392">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān
                                    Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">رشید الدین خان دهلوی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23268">Ṣawlat-i ghaz̤anfarīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23268">صولت غضنفریه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Selections from Rashīd al-Dīn Dihlavī's <title>Ṣawlat-i
                                        ghaz̤anfarīyah</title>, a refutation of the Shiʻa practice
                                    of temporary marriage (<term>mutʿah</term>), preceded by an
                                    introduction by the anonymous compiler. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Followed on <locus from="174v" to="175r">ff. 174v-175r</locus> by
                                    a list of points which Sunnis have disagreed with in <persName key="viaf_36805746">Dildār ʻAlī</persName>'s <title key="work_23074">Ṣavārim</title>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f010r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 10</ref>.
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>C.A. Storey, <title>Persian Literature: A Bio-bibliographical
                                        Survey</title>, in <title>Storey
                                            Online</title>
                           <biblScope>
                              <ref target="https://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/storey-online/12-law-2-COM_40102000#V4-0137" type="n/a">, vol.IV §137 </ref>
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
